CSSFunctionDescriptors.summary: NOTE Experimental The CSSFunctionDescriptors interface of the CSS Object Model represents the descriptors contained within a set of CSS declarations represented by a object.

remarks.para: A CSSFunctionDescriptors object is accessed via the property.

CSSFunctionDescriptorsResult.summary: NOTE Experimental The result property of the interface returns a string representing a result descriptor, if one exists in the associated set of declarations.
CSSFunctionDescriptorsResult.value: A string.If no result descriptor exists in the associated set of declarations, an empty string is returned.
